            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the greens are cooking, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>and<strong> soy sauce</strong> in 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>stock</strong></p><p>Heat a pot over a medium heat and once hot, add 15g <span class=\"text-purple\">[25g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[30g]</span> <strong>butter</strong>, then once melted, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs until a sandy paste has formed</p><p>Whisk in the<strong> stock </strong>and cook for 4-5 min, stirring occasionally – this is your <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
